    "updated_at": "2015-06-19T21:27:51Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I believe this is where I say that one can be simplified to the same 2 lines I posted above. (It is 4-year-old code, so no wonder it doesn't really measure up to our current standards.)\nBut then again, I see no point in arguing over something so simple.\nOn the other hand, on the off chance that someone does indeed screw up their YAML sufficiently, your fix won't kick in and we're back to the same crash.\nAlthough the way to crash (color picker) is now disabled, so...\nBut in the end, this violates the braces style rule, and fixes the problem, but leaves a tiny whole through which it can resurface.\nMy suggestion is to let it crash, but here, so it is very easy to determine what went wrong by only using the stack trace, or using the utility with `--check-yaml` to tell you.\n\nWow, I really wanted to merge it and be done with it without more arguing. Guess I couldn't.\n"
